The epic has been written to `/home/stephan/src/FairEmail/docs/epics/3.5-mark-as-read-on-view-on-scroll-or-never.md`. It covers:

- **Auto-mark-read on expand** with configurable delay (Off through 60s)
- **Per-account auto-seen override** to disable auto-marking for specific accounts
- **Peek semantics** ensuring server-side fetch never implicitly marks read
- **Auto-read on move** (archive/trash/file implies read)
- **Undo grace period** for triage actions (configurable, default 5s)
- **Manual toggle** via button, context menu, keyboard shortcut, and swipe
- **Threading interaction** (auto-mark = single message; manual toggle = whole thread)
- **Close-on-unread** workflow accelerator
- **Server synchronization** of read-state changes

Six open questions documented, including the "on scroll" naming ambiguity (the source app has no distinct scroll-based trigger — it's expand-plus-delay).
